Reasoning: The paper deals with the information theoretic structure of measurements performed by distributed systems, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the use of probabilistic cellular automata and presheafs suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the quantification of information generated by measurements, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The concept of context-dependence and decomposability of measurements could also suggest that it belongs to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories, respectively.
